        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
The attitudes I'm seeing here make me sick.

Alot of the problem here IS the guild B types, who believe that the "uber" mobs are theirs to do with as they please and to hell with anyone else who wants a few tries.  Guilds like these often perma-kill certain mobs on my server, and its freaking ridiculous.

Sad enough to say, they can get away with it. Simply because there is nothing inherently wrong with what they are doing. They will sit pretty and justify themselves with this (which is EXACTLY what you all do).

Simply put:  Is guild B wrong? No. Are they being asses? YES. If people were a little nicer, and considerate once in a while, I'm sure there'd be a lot more happier people.  No one cares though, its all about themselves, and damn everyone else.

Guild B should have given Guild A one more shot, after that its more or less apparent that Guild A can't do it.  Besides that, Guild B would have been waiting for one attempt.

On another note:  How many of you are in guild A or guild B type guilds?  I'm sure there's a direct corrolation to your answers.  Oh, I am not currently in a guild myself, but am a PM for a guild with the power of guild B.  You know what?  That guild is one of THE most highly respected guilds on the server, simply because they WILL give people that other chance.

