        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Guild A finds out that Gorenaire is up in dreadlands and mobilizes a force to take her out.  The force arrives and finds that no one else is around and Gore is happily playing with herself.  Guild A pulls her and due to a couple unfortunate occurances, gets wiped out when Gorenaire is at about 35%.  The clerics were bound in BW at the dreadlands entrance and upon respawning at their bind points after the death, notice a very large force of Guild B amassing, ready to enter dreadlands.  The clerics zone in to dreadlands to start CR and inform the Guild A that Guild B has intentions to possibly take Gore.  Guildleader A messages Guildleader B and tells them they are gonna give her another try once they CR.  Guildleader B tells them that they had their shot and to step aside so they can take out Gorenaire.  Despite pleas of Guildleader A, Guild B not only pulls Gorenaire but pulls her close enough so that her AE is hitting Guild A's corpse recovery.</P><P>Does guild A have a right at anohter try since they were there first?</P><P>or</P><P>Was guild B in the right to have their shot?</P><P>Before any of you pull out the ridiculous PnP crap, don't bother.  We all know that PnP dictates that guild B should have a turn now.  I'm talking about flat out MORALS, not PnP.  </P><P>So, who was in the right, A or B?</P><P><BR><font color=red><b>Fasz </b></font id=red><BR><font color=black>57 Defiler </font id=black><BR><font color=blue><i>Bertoxx </font id=blue></i><BR>The Company</P><P><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99189" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99189</a></font></td>
